          <avActivityHighlights>In these regions the avalanche situation is mostly favourable.</avActivityHighlights>
          <avActivityComment>Little snow will fall until late morning. Until the afternoon the weather will be cloudy. &lt;br/&gt; Currently there are favourable conditions mostly. In these regions the avalanche prone locations are rare and the danger is level 1 (low).</avActivityComment>
          <snowpackStructureComment>Below approximately 2800 m: The snowpack is fairly homogeneous and its surface has a melt-freeze crust. &lt;br/&gt; Above approximately 3000 m, shady slopes: The snowpack is dry and its surface consists of loosely bonded snow lying on a crust that is strong in many cases. &lt;br/&gt; &lt;br/&gt; As a consequence of mild temperatures and solar radiation the snowpack consolidated at the weekend. This applies in particular on steep sunny slopes at high altitude, and in all aspects at low and intermediate altitudes. &lt;br/&gt; &lt;br/&gt; Below approximately 2400 m only a little snow is lying on south facing slopes.</snowpackStructureComment>
